Czech CNB fixes crown + 4 . 62 pct vs mark / usd basket . The Czech National Bank ( CNB ) fixed the crown at 27 . 922 to the dollar after Tuesday ' s fixing at 28 . 017 , and at 16 . 894 to the mark from 16 . 944 . The above rates imply a deviation from the midpoint of the central bank ' s mark / dollar basket of + 4 . 62 percent , up from Tuesday ' s + 4 . 32 - deviation . During the minute when the central bank calculated the fixing , the crown was on the interbank market at + 4 . 59 percent . The crown fixing is announced daily at about 1140 CET ( 1040 GMT ) and is within plus / minus 7 . 5 percent of the mark / dollar basket midpoint calculated between 11 : 30 : 00 and 11 : 30 : 59 CET . - - Prague Newsroom , 42 - 2 - 2423 - 0003 
